==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[stypticus]], from Greek [[στυπτικος]], from [[στυφειν]] ‘to contract’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'stɪptɪk/

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|styptic}}
# bringing about contraction of tissues, especially to stop bleeding
#:*'''1973''': The growth on top was a scrubby plant, unknown anywhere else on Malta, which was believed to have '''styptic''' qualities – it could staunch bleeding when packed on top of a wound — Nicholas Monsarrat, ''The Kapillan of Malta''

